---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import DownloadCta from "../components/DownloadCta.astro";
import { withBase } from "../config.mjs";
---

<Base
  title="About KaiZenly+ (KaiZenly Plus) — The Story Behind the App"
  path="/about/"
  description="KaiZenly+ (also known as KaiZenly Plus or KaiZenly) is built by a solo student developer based in Pakistan. Learn the story behind the app and the meaning of the name — inspired by the Japanese philosophy of Kaizen."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg" style="margin-top:10px">Built by a student, for calmer days</h1>

      <div class="prose" style="margin-top:24px">
        <p class="lede">
          I’m a solo student developer based in <strong>Pakistan</strong>. I built KaiZenly+ first
          for myself, after trying a lot of focus, habit, and journaling apps and never finding one
          privacy-first app that combined these features properly.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most apps did one thing well — blocking, or habits, or mood — but pulled my data to a
          server, asked me to log in, or wrapped everything in ads and pressure. I wanted something
          calmer and more private: a single place to build habits, protect focus, reflect, and
          understand my patterns, with everything staying on my own device.
        </p>
        <p>
          I have a limited budget, so I didn’t build a backend or buy servers. That constraint
          turned into the app’s biggest strength: KaiZenly+ is local-first by design. When I felt it
          was genuinely useful, I thought other students and people might benefit too — so I’m
          sharing it. Every feature is <strong>free right now</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          If, in the future, server, backend, AI, or MCP features are added and they involve real
          costs, some of those might become paid. But that’s a possible future direction — not a
          promise, and not part of the app today.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">Why the name “KaiZenly+”?</h2>
        <p>
          The name is inspired by <strong>Kaizen</strong> (改善) — a Japanese word commonly
          understood as <em>“change for the better.”</em> It comes from two ideas: <strong>Kai</strong>
          (change) and <strong>Zen</strong> (for the better). In modern use, Kaizen is closely tied
          to <strong>continuous improvement</strong> — the belief that small, consistent steps create
          powerful long-term change.
        </p>
        <p>The name breaks into four meaningful parts:</p>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li><strong>Kai</strong> — change, progress, and the decision to become better.</li>
          <li><strong>Zen</strong> — calm, focus, and balance; peaceful productivity without stress.</li>
          <li><strong>ly</strong> — a modern, lifestyle ending that makes improvement feel natural and daily.</li>
          <li><strong>+</strong> — a complete system, more than a single-feature app.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Together, KaiZenly+ means: <strong>improve your life calmly, one small step at a time.</strong>
          That idea runs through everything — one better habit, one focused session, one honest
          journal entry, one mood check-in, one distraction avoided. Small actions, repeated, become
          real change.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif">The philosophy</h2>
        <p>
          KaiZenly+ doesn’t believe in pressure, perfectionism, or guilt-driven productivity. It
          believes in gentle progress, personal space, and realistic systems — calm focus instead of
          chaotic hustle. The app should feel like a quiet daily companion, not a strict coach.
        </p>

        <h2 class="display-sm serif" id="contact">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions, feedback, or just want to say hi? Reach me at
          <a href="mailto:kaizenlyplus@gmail.com">kaizenlyplus@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:36px">
        <DownloadCta />
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={withBase("/why-kaizenly/")}>Why KaiZenly+</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
